REMARK   3  S-ADENOSYLMETHIONINE (SAM) HAS BEEN MODELLED IN THE CO-SUBSTRATE    
REMARK   3  BINDING POCKET BUT ONLY PARTS OF THE MOLECULE CORRESPONDING TO ITS  
REMARK   3  BASE AND AMINO ACID END ARE RESOLVED IN THE ELECTRON DENSITY. THE   
REMARK   3  CENTRAL PART OF THE CO-SUBSTRATE COULD NOT BE UNAMBIGUOUSLY TRACED, 
REMARK   3  WHICH MAY BE DUE TO ITS DECOMPOSITION TO HOMOSERINE LACTONE (HSL)   
REMARK   3  AND METHYLTHIOADENOSINE (MTA).                                      
REMARK   3  THE RESIDUAL DIFFERENCE DENSITY NEXT TO THE SUBSTRATE BASE LIKELY   
REMARK   3  RESULTS FROM THE RESIDUAL PRESENCE OF THE ACTIVE SITE LOOP IN THE " 
REMARK   3  IN" CONFORMATION BUT THE OCCUPANCY OF THIS CONFORMER WAS TOO LOW    
REMARK   3  TO BE INCLUDED IN THE MODEL.                                        
